        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix OTLP log trace correlation",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- fix OTLP log correlation for OpenClaw-owned logger records emitted inside active diagnostic trace scopes\n- keep explicit logger-supplied trace objects untrusted so plugin/user-provided trace IDs cannot spoof OTLP ancestry\n- extend the OTEL QA smoke to fail unless exported log records include trace/span correlation IDs while default log bodies remain placeholders\n\nFixes #91865 for the trace/span correlation portion. This intentionally does not change default OTLP log body export; log bodies remain gated by content capture.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` initially found one actionable test assertion issue; fixed it and reran clean: `autoreview clean: no accepted/actionable findings reported`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/logging/diagnostic-log-events.test.ts extensions/diagnostics-otel/src/service.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/qa-otel-smoke.test.ts`\n- Crabbox/Testbox live E2E: `tbx_01ktwd5egrdrx7fa924hzj7hnf`, provider `blacksmith-testbox`, command `corepack pnpm qa:otel:collector-smoke --output-dir .artifacts/qa-e2e/issue-91865-fixed-testbox`, exit `0`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: OTLP log records emitted from OpenClaw-owned active diagnostic trace scopes now carry OTLP trace/span correlation context while preserving placeholder log bodies by default.\nReal environment tested: Blacksmith Testbox through Crabbox on Linux with a real `otel/opentelemetry-collector:0.104.0` container and mock OpenAI QA provider.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `corepack pnpm qa:otel:collector-smoke --output-dir .artifacts/qa-e2e/issue-91865-fixed-testbox`\nEvidence after fix: Testbox `tbx_01ktwd5egrdrx7fa924hzj7hnf` passed the updated smoke, which decodes OTLP log `traceId`/`spanId` fields and fails if no log record includes both IDs.\nObserved result after fix: `qa-otel-smoke: passed spans=17 metrics=17 logs=9 traces=3 metricRequests=3 logRequests=3`\nWhat was not tested: A third-party production OTLP backend UI; the proof validates the OTLP payload through a real collector and decoded receiver.\n",
